body: "## Evidence (Nightly Validation run 29142565592, commit 4b6ca51d, 2026-07-11)\n- Only macos-latest / Node 24 red; 269/270 test files pass. Single failure: `tests/integration/init-path-guard.integration.spec.ts:167` (the GH-495 root-layout regression test).\n- Assertion diff: expected `pm_root: /var/folders/.../pm-cli-test-BX16dC/root-layout-ws`, received `/private/var/folders/...` — macOS `/var` is a symlink to `/private/var`; `pm probe root --json` returns the canonical (realpath'd) root, the test compares against the logical mkdtemp path.\n- Deterministic, NOT a flake: first nightly containing the test (merged with the GH-495 fix after the 07-10 nightly ran). PR CI matrices do not cover macOS, so it only surfaces nightly.\n\n## Root cause\n`tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts:314` creates the workspace via `mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), \"pm-cli-test-\"))` WITHOUT canonicalizing. The identical class was fixed by pm-gf6f (\"fixed macOS realpath mismatch by canonicalizing mkdtemp output\") but only inside the extension-command unit spec — the shared integration helper never got the fix, so every future integration test comparing absolute paths re-inherits the trap.\n\n## Fix shape\nCanonicalize once at the source: `tempRoot = await realpath(await mkdtemp(...))` in withTempPmPath. Product behavior is correct (probe returning the canonical root is desirable identity semantics); this is test-infrastructure-side only. Sweep other `mkdtemp` sites under tests/ for the same omission while there."
